description: A woman sits on a couch in a living room, speaking on a corded telephone, surrounded by three fishbowls filled with numerous tadpoles. She expresses frustration about the unexpected domestic burden of being stuck at home with amphibian offspring, which resulted from kissing a frog who turned into a prince. This presents an absurd and ironic twist on the classic fairy tale narrative. The presence of a mop beside her emphasizes the mundane reality of her situation. Her complaint highlights the unforeseen and overwhelming consequences of a magical transformation.
caption: “Well that's how it happened, Sylvia. ... I kissed this frog, he turns into a prince, we get married, and WHAM! ... I'm stuck at home with a bunch of pollywogs.”
